co.paralleluniverse.data.record

Interface Record<R>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractRecord

    public interface Record<R>

    A record made of some Fields with values. Field values are read and set with the get(field} and set(field, value) methods, respectively.

      • read

        void read(ObjectInput in,
        int numFields)
          throws IOException

        Reads the record’s contents from a serialized form in an ObjectInput, only reading the first numFields fields from the stream. This is useful when dealing with reading a serialized form of a different version of the record, which has fields added.

        Parameters:
        in -
        numFields - the number of fields to read from the stream
        Throws:
        IOException
